        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I got some problems here\n\nI'm trying to use Zend_Search_Lucene to index documments from a Digital Library, so the some documments are large.\nWhen i try to index all of them at once (they're about 1024 documments) Zend trows a exception of trying to allocate more memory than allowed, so i try to index around 20 documments for turn.\nIf i try to index without optimize, around the 100 documment i get a lot of the error \n\nPhp Notice: Undefined offset: xxx in ...Zend\/Search\/Lucene\/Index\/SegmentInfo.php on line165\n\nthen get a loop (maybe?) in\n\nPhp Notice: Unitializeds strinf offset: xxxx in ...Zend\/Search\/Lucene\/Storage\/File.php on line 322\n\nIf i try to optimize a index each time i add the 20 documments, i get this error in the 21 documment added\n\nI dont know what to do\n\n\n\n\nEDIT: Hey people, i got a solution a while ago, and just forget to post here.\nI add all documments first and them optimize them.\nThe problem is that i cant add a documment in a index that already existis, i got to make a new one, adding all documments again, but if i make a new, no problem"
        },
