                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=joshs633",
                        "name": "joshs633",
                        "displayName": "Josh Schumacher",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "What is your php.ini memory allocation set to?  I have some indexing and optimization scripts that require me to ini_set the memory limit to 1024M or else they fail.  Zend_Search_Lucene is a memory HOG!",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=joshs633",
                        "name": "joshs633",
                        "displayName": "Josh Schumacher",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-07-18T17:50:58.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-07-18T17:50:58.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48511",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This isn't a bug in Zend_Search_Lucene.  It is a memory hog by nature, and so if you want to process large indexes you will need to bump up your PHP memory limit settings.  \n\nI couldn't reproduce the PHP notices that the OP alluded to, either. \n\nClosing as \"Not an Issue\"",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
